Dangote Sugar Refinery’s revenue performance in the first half financial statement has seen a decline from N84bn in Q2 2018 to N80.4bn in Q2 2019, marking a 4.4 per cent decrease. Profit Before Tax (PBT) for the period under review also decreased by 14.4 per cent to N19.9bn, down from N17bn that was recorded in Q2 2018. Profit After Tax (PAT) also declined to N10.9bn in Q2 2019 as against N12.7bn during the comparable period in 2018. This indicates a 13.7 per cent decrease. Earnings Per Share: Basic earnings per share in Q2 2019 was N0.92 as against N1.07 in Q2 2018. In the same vein, diluted earnings per share in Q2 was N0.92 as against N1.07. Q2: 45 firms post results on NSE Fidson revenue increases by 128% in Q2 42 coys’ half year profits surge by N31bn Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin